1. Convert the Python Script into an Executable
First, convert your Python script into an executable file using pyinstaller. This ensures it can run independently of your Python installation.

Steps:
Install PyInstaller:
    pip install pyinstaller
Create an executable:
    PyInstaller --onefile --noconsole BatteryMeter.py
    --onefile: Bundles everything into a single .exe file.
    --noconsole: Hides the terminal window when running.
The resulting executable will be in the dist/ folder.

2. Add the Executable to Windows Startup
    Press Win + R, type shell:startup, and press Enter.
    Copy the generated .exe file into the Startup folder.
    It will now run automatically when Windows starts.
